            {"id":4,"title":"AI System Design","difficulty":"advanced","desc":"Design the complete technical architecture for an AI customer support system handling 10k tickets/day.","instruction":"Components, data flow, scalability, cost estimate, SLA.","success_criteria":"All components named. Data flow described. Scale numbers addressed. Cost estimated. SLA defined.","example":"Design an AI customer support system for 10k tickets/day: 1) Architecture diagram (ASCII) 2) Components: intake, classification, RAG, response generation, human escalation, CSAT 3) Data flow from ticket submission to response 4) Scale: how it handles 10x traffic spikes 5) Monthly infra cost estimate 6) SLA: response time, accuracy target, escalation rate"},
            {"id":5,"title":"AI Evaluation Framework","difficulty":"advanced","desc":"Build an evaluation framework for an AI product before launch. Define what good looks like.","instruction":"Metrics, test dataset design, human eval process, launch threshold.","success_criteria":"Quantitative metrics defined. Test set design specified. Human eval process described. Launch threshold set.","example":"Design a pre-launch evaluation framework for an AI contract review tool: 1) Define 5 metrics (accuracy, recall for risk clauses, false negative rate, latency, user satisfaction) 2) Test dataset design: how many docs, what mix of types 3) Human eval: who reviews, rubric they use, inter-rater reliability 4) Launch threshold: minimum score per metric to ship 5) Post-launch monitoring plan"},
            {"id":6,"title":"AI Onboarding Flow","difficulty":"intermediate","desc":"Design the first-time user experience for an AI tool that needs to learn about the user.","instruction":"Onboarding steps, what data to collect, how to use it immediately to show value.","success_criteria":"Under 5 steps. Value shown before onboarding ends. Data collection justified. Aha moment defined.","example":"Design a 5-step onboarding for an AI email assistant: 1) What to ask the user (role, company, email volume) 2) What to connect (Gmail/Outlook) 3) First action that shows immediate value 4) The aha moment (specific, timed) 5) What to do if user drops off at step 3. Goal: time-to-value under 3 minutes."},
            {"id":7,"title":"Responsible AI Checklist","difficulty":"intermediate","desc":"Build a responsible AI product checklist for a hiring tool that screens CVs.","instruction":"Cover: bias testing, transparency, opt-out, audit trail, regulatory compliance.","success_criteria":"Bias testing methodology. Transparency to candidates. Opt-out mechanism. Audit trail. GDPR/Equality Act mentioned.","example":"Build a responsible AI checklist for a CV screening tool: 1) BIAS: How to test for gender/ethnic/age bias, what threshold triggers a halt 2) TRANSPARENCY: What do candidates know about AI involvement? 3) OPT-OUT: Can candidates request human review? 4) AUDIT: What data to keep, for how long, who can access 5) COMPLIANCE: UK Equality Act 2010, GDPR Article 22 (automated decisions), ICO guidance"},
            {"id":8,"title":"AI Sales Pitch","difficulty":"intermediate","desc":"Write a 2-minute investor pitch for an AI product. Problem, solution, market, traction, ask.","instruction":"5 sections, 24 seconds each, no jargon, specific numbers.","success_criteria":"5 sections present. Specific market size number. Traction metric real or realistic. Ask specific (amount + use of funds).","example":"Write a 2-minute investor pitch for [AI product]: PROBLEM (24 sec): Specific pain, who has it, cost of the problem SOLUTION (24 sec): How your AI solves it, the key differentiator MARKET (24 sec): TAM/SAM/SOM with real numbers, why now TRACTION (24 sec): Specific numbers: users, revenue, growth rate, notable customers ASK (24 sec): Amount, use of funds, what milestone it gets you to"},
